rComments: Dr. Murck and Dr. Havelka make an amazing duo team. Although, I would recommend speeding up Dr. Murck's lecture videos as she talks very slow.
Fav prof at UTM. Prof. Murck cares about her students and clearly loves what she teaches. I try and take as many of her courses as I can.
Interesting lectures
Great prof, easy course if you have a science background
Great prof

JGE is an interesting course. Knowing the course material will easily give you a good mark on the midterm. Murck is a great prof, super approachable before, during and after lecture. Study moderate/hard and you'll be fine. There are assignments and a paper, so one can easily do well on this course. Take advantage of her, few are as nice and kind!
tests are too hard, and she expects us to know all the information. The course requires a lot of work, and the videos for each week are way too long.
Test is hard but she expected us to remember every single word in this class!!!

Overall it was a good experience. There was a lot of work - quizzes and assignments every few weeks. But they were not too difficult. The midterm and exam was challenging but not too difficult or surprising. If you study your best, you'll get the grades you want. She's also quite reasonable with the grading.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Prof is great, a little boring at times. This course is not a bird course, its boring and its lengthy and I HATED most of the content. It just wasn't my thing. It was the last thing I wanted to do and obviously that showed in my grade. Don't take it bc you think its a bird course. This class actually brought down my GPA a lot bc its full year..
Great prof, really good course. Not necessarily "bird" but definitely easy if you put in some time. Be wary of the term test, it brings marks down.
Great at explaining concepts.

Definitely the best prof I've had! She is so very thorough with all of the material she teaches, and she has such a passion and enjoyment for teaching. If you show up to lecture and concentrate on what she's talking about you WILL do well. I've not even an env major but I wish I could have her for more courses in the future!
Definitely one of the best profs I've had. She is extremely thorough and explains concepts very well, is clearly very knowledgable, cares about her students and wants them to do well.
Great professor! She's so nice and truly cares about her students. Easy A if you attend lectures and take good notes.

Hands down, one of the best Profs I have had in university so far. Very helpful and informative. She explains everything in detail. Lecture slides were very helpful. Quizzes were easy. Midterm was long but do-able. Would highly recommend this course.

I took this class 3.5 years ago. It`s very different now and I don`t think she teaches it anymore! I loved the prof, but hated the course so much! The midterm and the exam were extremely brutal as she gave us no preparations ahead of time. Overall, she is a good prof.

Prof is a lot of fun and really enjoys the subject shes teaching. I hated the course but she made it enjoyable. The exam was super easy because of the clear and concise review she and hevelka provided. Great profs!

Easiest final exam I have ever written ever in my life! Actually, all components of this course are easy and do not require so much effort. Prof is always excited about what she is teaching. She is the most accessible and approachable Prof ever. Take this course!(I'm a commerce specialist)
She's a very good prof. She explains everything very well, so you don't even need the textbook. Also, prof Murck and Havelka give you the notes for the course. :)
BEST professor I have ever talked to. I major in Social Sciences and was not into Sciences at all: thanks to Professor, I feel much better about Science :)
worst prof ever uncaring, rude,  and ruined my university experience . should not be a prof

Took this course for science credit, ended up changing programs due to the amazing experience I had. She is enthusiastic, helpful, fair. She gives ample opportunity to get marks in a variety of different ways (quizzes, test, assignments etc). Go to class and participate (iClicker) and you'll do well! Exam was tough, but fair
The absolute best of the best at UTM. She is THE most helpful professor you will ever have. She is very clear and descriptive; her lectures are very interesting. I wish I had her for all my classes.
Great Prof! I thoroughly enjoyed her course. It was interesting, and she's very enthusiastic about teaching her craft. The grading was super fair and the material was interesting. :)
AMAZING PROF!! So helpful, understanding and passionate about teaching
an excellent prof. !
Good prof.

She is supportive, guiding, and always on the side of her students. Listen to her lecture and take notes for what she says. Her course stay very interesting because of the material and because she invites professors to guest-lecture on topics that they specialize in. She deserves the continued respect and support of her students and peers.
Good prof.  I had a bad mark but I didn't study and rarely attended lectures.  My sense is for this class you need to do one of those two things.

Probably the most caring professor at UTM! She is extremely flexible and helps with everything. She even offered students to do the course online and not attend class! The material is interesting, and it's an easy course to take to fill the distribution requirements and to boost your mark.  Don't buy the textbook - it's a giant waste of money.  All the lecture slides get posted.

Do yourself a favour, don't buy the text book. The only reason it's required is because she wrote it and she obviously wants to boost her sales, but it is completely useless for tests and exams. Don't pay attention to the slides, but rather, to what she says in class (which may be hard... because she's quite dull).
She is a good, caring teacher... but the class isn't that interesting.

best prof! great class!
great prof. learned alot. loved the class

She does know what she is talking about, very smart and friendly Prof. If you are interested to learn more about "natural hazards" take the course. If you are not interested in the subject, you will waste your time.
The course material is a cake but the term tests can be problematic since they consist of 100% short answers (No MC). Recommended for non-sci students who are looking for easy 1.0 sci credit.

ENV100 is not a very difficult course if you take the time to review and study the lecture notes before each quiz. Some of the lectures are pretty interesting but it also depends on how interested you are in environment. Murck is a very good prof and is very helpful if you have any questions.
This course should be canceled. I am not kidding!

I absolutely agree with the previous comments. It is impossible to understand from those guest speakers. And this course is just SO BORING,I find it very hard to concentrate in lectures b/c of monotones. Many ppl go on facebook during lectures..and leave early.. lol

Horrible class!! If you are planning to take this course as an elective, don't take it b/c you will regret for sure. The dispersion of the marks is really small, which means if the class average is 60, I would say most of you will get around that mark. Very difficult to get high marks. Just dont take this course!!
horrible proff every.

Murck is an excellent teacher.Best I've had so far at UTM.The course is terrific and well organized. I chose my post as GEOG b/c of this course. Stay on top of all readings and you will do excellent on the quizzes. The tests are harder so study efficiently, don't leave studying to the night before! If you are IN to school, you'll be in to Murck!

If you get 60's in this class you are either very dumb or don't study at all. Lectures are unnecessary. Study a good 2-3 hours for every quiz by reviewing the lecture notes a few times and you will dominate each and every quiz. Go to the lectures for the bonus participation days if you want.

I'm a UTM Grad and Prof Murck was one of the best Prof's I've ever had.  Clear, concise and full of real-world insight.  Tests are about average on the difficulty scale, but she'll teach you more than most Prof's out there.  I highly recommend her courses.
Great teacher, great person, just sometimes confusing and lacks clarity. Demanding, but good. No complaints, other than the occaisional ramble!
U ROCK Murck

She is such a good professor, her lessons are easy to understand and follow, and she makes you interested in what you are learning. The tests are not bad if you study you'll ace them.

One of the best. Personable, interesting speaker 95% of the time. Willing to engage you in conversation both in and out of the classroom.

most of the course was taught by other profs. hardly looked at the book or my own notes. online notes had almost all the answers to the multiple-choice-question-based term tests. i'm sure a lot of people took this for their birdcoursebutaverageclassaverag

Class is so boring, though she does show movies to the class every Friday (a nice break).  Tests are multiple choice but are so hard.  Do not take this cource if you don't have to.  More then half of the students do not get the marks they desire. Beware
I loved her!! If you can, try taking ENV 100 with her...definitely a mark booster.  Very interesting course too.
